<p>New Haven's cold climate demands robust HVAC systems capable of handling winter temperatures that frequently drop below freezing. For this climate zone, heat pumps with SEER ratings of 16-20 and HSPF ratings of 9.5 or higher provide optimal efficiency. Cold climate heat pumps, also known as mini-splits or ductless systems, are particularly effective in New Haven as they can operate efficiently even when outdoor temperatures reach -15¬∞F. These systems provide both heating and cooling, making them ideal year-round solutions.</p>

