<h2>New Haven Energy Incentives</h2>
<p>New Haven residents have access to multiple incentive programs that significantly reduce the cost of solar and HVAC installations. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% credit on the total cost of solar panel systems through 2032, making it an excellent time to invest in solar energy. This credit applies to all system components including panels, inverters, mounting equipment, and installation labor.</p>

<p>Connecticut offers additional state-level incentives through the Green Bank's Residential Solar Investment Program, which provides performance-based incentives for solar installations. UI customers may also benefit from net metering programs that allow excess solar production to be credited back to the utility at retail rates. For HVAC systems, the federal tax credit covers 30% of qualifying heat pump installations through 2032, while Connecticut's Energize CT program offers rebates up to \$500 for high-efficiency heating and cooling equipment. Low-income residents may qualify for additional assistance through the Home Energy Solutions program.</p>

