<p>New Haven's coastal location and cold climate create specific installation requirements for both solar and HVAC systems. Solar panels must be rated for high wind loads due to occasional coastal storms, while mounting systems should be corrosion-resistant to handle salt air exposure in areas closer to Long Island Sound. Snow load considerations are important, with panels typically installed at steeper angles to promote snow shedding during winter months.</p>

<p>HVAC installations in New Haven must account for the city's urban heat island effect during summers and harsh winter conditions. Proper insulation and air sealing are crucial for system efficiency, particularly in older homes that comprise much of New Haven's housing stock. Heat pump outdoor units should be positioned to avoid snow drifts and equipped with cold-weather packages for optimal performance during Connecticut's challenging winter conditions.</p>

